<item>
            <title>[LU-15405] Imporove dom-performance IOR Test</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15405</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This bug addresses two issue with present test_IOR test under dom-performance&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. IOR randomize access(-z) requires blocksize &amp;gt; transferSize Adjust tsize accordingly&#160; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;ERROR: IOR will randomize access within a block and repeats the same pattern for all segments, therefore choose blocksize &amp;gt; transferSize, (ior.c:1485)&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. Adjust iteration count of IOR to 1/4 as higher count was making MDS run out of space&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;ior ERROR: write() failed, errno 28, No space left on device (aiori-POSIX.c:451)&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
